title.narrative: QUALITY INCLUSIVE EDUCATION

description.narrative: Authorities at national and subnational levels, communities, schools and caregivers have an increased capacity to address harmful social norms, to generate demand for and provide services, as well as to support an environment conducive to the equitable access of disadvantaged children and adolescents, especially those from Roma communities and those with disabilities, to quality, inclusive education., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The social inclusion of all children and adolescents, especially vulnerable ones, is supported by quality, equitable and coordinated health, education and child protection systems and protective social norms.

description.narrative: UNICEF’s technical assistance and advocacy resulted in significant achievements: the incorporation of QIE in the ‘Educated Romania’ strategy for 20212027, the recovery and resilience plan and the national strategy and operational plan for child rights. A new module on school desegregation was developed and included in Romania’s integrated education system, a standard cost for ante-preschool education was defined and approved for the first time and the ratio of school counsellors to students was reduced;from;800:1;to;500:1.The National Student Council (CNE) produced its first brochure for members of Parliament and 13,716 students received support through the e-learning platform. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
